    "Validation Failure Risks": "1) Failure to capture fine-scale channels due to insufficient collocation points or model capacity; 2) Poor convergence from high contrast causing vanishing/exploding gradients in NN models; 3) Surrogate overfitting to training permeability distribution, failing out-of-distribution (e.g., unseen channel patterns); 4) Inaccurate enforcement of boundary conditions (especially Neumann) leading to non-physical predictions; 5) For surrogate, computational cost of data generation may outweigh benefits if number of queries is moderate; 6) Physics-informed loss may dominate data loss, causing model to ignore actual simulation data if used. Mitigation: use multiscale architecture, adaptive collocation, rigorous uncertainty quantification (e.g., ensemble methods), and test on held-out permeability fields with similar statistics."
