    "Validation Failure Risks": "Failure risks include: (i) mass drift due to inadequate enforcement of conservation – quantitative monitoring: compute total mass at each iteration; tolerance: relative drift < 1e-6 per 1000 iterations; cadence: every 100 iterations during training and at saved checkpoints. (ii) failure to resolve sharp interfaces if ε is too small relative to collocation density – use adaptive sampling and monitor interface width resolution. (iii) spectral bias leading to low-frequency dominance – mitigate with Fourier features or multi-scale architecture. (iv) optimization getting stuck in trivial solution (e.g., uniform φ) – enforce IC strongly and use progressive ε annealing. (v) violation of boundary conditions – assess L_bc convergence and validate against analytical solutions or finite-difference simulations. (vi) training instability from stiff PDE – use causal training (time marching) or curriculum learning."
  }
}

